The paper discusses methods for optimizing the performance of machine learning algorithms for defect prediction in software analytics. This falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of evolutionary algorithms and optimization techniques also suggests a possible fit with artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). The mention of low intrinsic dimensionality and the need to match optimization algorithms to specific problems suggests a possible connection to control systems (cs.SY).
